{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":950,"text":"Thousands of years from now,"},{"time":3088,"text":"we'll look back at the first\ncentury of computing"},{"time":6960,"text":"as a fascinating but very peculiar time --"},{"time":11096,"text":"the only time in history where humans\nwere reduced to live in 2D space,"},{"time":16126,"text":"interacting with technology\nas if we were machines;"},{"time":20069,"text":"a singular, 100-year period\nin the vastness of time"},{"time":25310,"text":"where humans communicated,"},{"time":28022,"text":"were entertained and managed their lives"},{"time":30697,"text":"from behind a screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32395,"text":"Today, we spend most of our time\ntapping and looking at screens."},{"time":38762,"text":"What happened to interacting\nwith each other?"},{"time":43040,"text":"I don't know about you, but I feel limited"},{"time":45735,"text":"inside this 2D world\nof monitors and pixels."},{"time":49751,"text":"And it is this very limitation"},{"time":51840,"text":"and my desire to connect with people"},{"time":54280,"text":"that inspires me as a creator."},{"time":56292,"text":"Put simply: I want\nto create a new reality,"},{"time":59667,"text":"a reality where technology brings\nus infinitely closer to each other,"},{"time":65398,"text":"a reality where people, not devices,"},{"time":68612,"text":"are the center of everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70998,"text":"I dream of a reality where technology\nsenses what we see, touch and feel;"},{"time":77724,"text":"a reality where technology\nno longer gets in our way,"},{"time":81059,"text":"but instead embraces who we are."},{"time":84328,"text":"I dream of technology"},{"time":86728,"text":"on a human path."},{"time":88878,"text":"We have all experienced technology"},{"time":90910,"text":"that enables people\nto act more like people,"},{"time":94236,"text":"products that enable natural interactions,\nvoice controls or biometrics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103476,"text":"This is the next step in the evolution."},{"time":107330,"text":"This is Microsoft HoloLens,"},{"time":109309,"text":"the first fully untethered\nholographic computer."},{"time":113644,"text":"Devices like this will bring\n3D holographic content"},{"time":117861,"text":"right into our world,"},{"time":119804,"text":"enhancing the way we experience life"},{"time":121885,"text":"beyond our ordinary range of perceptions."},{"time":125233,"text":"Now, I'm not thinking\nabout a distant future."},{"time":129844,"text":"I'm talking about today."},{"time":131958,"text":"We are already seeing\ncar companies like Volvo"},{"time":135126,"text":"designing cars differently with HoloLens;"},{"time":138077,"text":"universities like Case Western\nredefining the way medical students learn;"},{"time":142832,"text":"and my personal favorite,"},{"time":144744,"text":"NASA is using HoloLens\nto let scientists explore planets"},{"time":150115,"text":"holographically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151932,"text":"Now, this is important."},{"time":154194,"text":"By bringing holograms into our world,"},{"time":156660,"text":"I'm not just talking about a new device\nor a better computer."},{"time":160914,"text":"I'm talking about freeing ourselves\nfrom the 2D confines"},{"time":166341,"text":"of traditional computing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169334,"text":"Put it this way:"},{"time":170961,"text":"temporally adjusted, we're like\ncave people in computer terms."},{"time":175878,"text":"We've barely discovered charcoal"},{"time":177816,"text":"and started drawing\nthe first stick figures in our cave."},{"time":182925,"text":"Now, this is the perspective\nI apply to my work every single day."},{"time":188016,"text":"And now for the next few minutes,"},{"time":189991,"text":"I invite all of you to apply\nthe same perspective"},{"time":194314,"text":"to the journey ahead of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199461,"text":"Now, as I put this HoloLens on,"},{"time":202405,"text":"let me explain the setup a little bit."},{"time":204608,"text":"It's probably the most risky demo\nwe have ever done on any stage"},{"time":210004,"text":"with HoloLens,"},{"time":211262,"text":"and I can't think of a better place\nto do it than here at TED."},{"time":215221,"text":"Momentarily, I am going\nto be seeing holograms"},{"time":219019,"text":"right on this stage,"},{"time":220365,"text":"just as clearly as I can see all of you."},{"time":222645,"text":"Now at the same time,\nwe have also this special camera"},{"time":226307,"text":"that just walked in onstage"},{"time":228027,"text":"so that all of you can share\nin this experience with me"},{"time":231283,"text":"up on all the monitors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233917,"text":"So let's start our journey."},{"time":235296,"text":"And what better place\nto begin our journey,"},{"time":237756,"text":"than in the computer cave of 2D."},{"time":242978,"text":"Let's explore the world\nall around us with this new lens,"},{"time":247193,"text":"and understand the computer world\nfrom a brand new perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251673,"text":"The computer universe\nis both marvelous and primitive."},{"time":256933,"text":"It's a universe based on causality."},{"time":260112,"text":"As developers, we dream\nthe different causes"},{"time":263304,"text":"and then we program the different effects."},{"time":266084,"text":"Double click on an icon, that's a cause."},{"time":269582,"text":"Open an application, that's an effect."},{"time":273264,"text":"Now when we compare this\nto our physical universe,"},{"time":277535,"text":"it is overly constraining,"},{"time":279574,"text":"because our universe is not digital."},{"time":282747,"text":"Our universe is analog."},{"time":284662,"text":"Our universe doesn't think\nin terms of zero or one,"},{"time":289240,"text":"true or false, or black or white."},{"time":292663,"text":"We exist in a world\ngoverned by quantum physics,"},{"time":296933,"text":"a universe of zero and one\nboth at the same time,"},{"time":301880,"text":"a reality based on infinite\nprobabilities and shades of gray."},{"time":307384,"text":"You can see how these two worlds collide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311975,"text":"So why are screens so pervasive\nin our analog life?"},{"time":318366,"text":"We see screens from the moment we wake up,"},{"time":320991,"text":"to the moment we fall asleep."},{"time":323174,"text":"Why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324666,"text":"I think it's because computers\ngive us superpowers."},{"time":328393,"text":"Within the digital universe,\nwe have the power to displace space"},{"time":332123,"text":"and the power to displace time."},{"time":334381,"text":"It doesn't matter if you're using\ntechnology for entertainment,"},{"time":337741,"text":"productivity or communication."},{"time":340700,"text":"Think of it this way:"},{"time":341885,"text":"let's all go home tonight"},{"time":343289,"text":"and watch our favorite show on television."},{"time":346462,"text":"This is theater -- time\nand space displaced."},{"time":350634,"text":"As soon as I'm done with this TED Talk,"},{"time":352758,"text":"I'm going to immediately call\nmy lovely family in Seattle."},{"time":359261,"text":"That's displacement of space."},{"time":362088,"text":"Now, these are such great superpowers"},{"time":364335,"text":"that we put up with\nthe two-dimensional limitations"},{"time":367308,"text":"of our current digital world."},{"time":369121,"text":"But what if we didn't have to?"},{"time":371180,"text":"What if we could have\nthese same digital powers"},{"time":375168,"text":"in our world?"},{"time":377966,"text":"You can already see glimmers of this,"},{"time":380386,"text":"but I believe our children's children"},{"time":383062,"text":"will grow up in a world\ndevoid of 2D technology."},{"time":388079,"text":"It's remarkable to dream of this world,"},{"time":390518,"text":"a world where technology\ntruly understands us --"},{"time":394731,"text":"where we live, work and communicate --"},{"time":397285,"text":"with tools that enhance\nthe human experience,"},{"time":400971,"text":"not machines that limit our humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406642,"text":"So how do we get there?"},{"time":409182,"text":"For me, the answer required\nlooking at the problem"},{"time":413296,"text":"from a different perspective."},{"time":416930,"text":"It required sensing the world\nfrom the perspective of a machine."},{"time":422429,"text":"If you're a machine trying\nto sense our world,"},{"time":426055,"text":"how would you actually\nbreak the problem down?"},{"time":429137,"text":"You'd probably try to classify things"},{"time":431856,"text":"as a human,"},{"time":434205,"text":"an environment"},{"time":436999,"text":"or an object."},{"time":439973,"text":"But how would that machine\nthen interact with reality?"},{"time":445063,"text":"And I can think of three ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446712,"text":"First, as a machine,"},{"time":448902,"text":"I would observe or I would input reality."},{"time":453847,"text":"Speech recognition\nand biometric authentication"},{"time":456553,"text":"are great examples of a machine\ninteracting with humans"},{"time":459837,"text":"from an input perspective."},{"time":462481,"text":"Secondly, as a machine,"},{"time":464796,"text":"I could place digital information,\nor output information,"},{"time":469931,"text":"into reality."},{"time":471939,"text":"Holograms are examples of a machine\ninteracting with an environment"},{"time":476635,"text":"from an output perspective."},{"time":478968,"text":"Finally, as a machine,"},{"time":481110,"text":"I could exchange energy\nwith the world via haptics."},{"time":485800,"text":"Now, imagine being able to feel\nthe temperature of a virtual object,"},{"time":490416,"text":"or better yet, imagine pushing a hologram"},{"time":493659,"text":"and having it push you back\nwith equal force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497455,"text":"With this perspective,"},{"time":499186,"text":"we are able to collapse reality\ninto a simple matrix."},{"time":504172,"text":"Now here's a secret:"},{"time":505347,"text":"as an engineer, I get really excited"},{"time":507429,"text":"anytime I can reduce\nsomething to the matrix."},{"time":510783,"text":"From self-driving cars"},{"time":512846,"text":"to smartphones"},{"time":514459,"text":"to this holographic computer on my head,"},{"time":516805,"text":"machines are becoming capable\nof understanding our world."},{"time":521293,"text":"And they are starting to interact with us"},{"time":523852,"text":"in significantly more personal ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528197,"text":"Now, imagine having granular control"},{"time":531846,"text":"over everything in the world."},{"time":534780,"text":"Move the dial one way,"},{"time":538930,"text":"and you get reality."},{"time":541268,"text":"Move the dial the other way,"},{"time":545582,"text":"and you get virtual reality."},{"time":549748,"text":"Now, imagine dialing\nyour entire environment"},{"time":554863,"text":"between virtual and real worlds."},{"time":562462,"text":"I love it down here."},{"time":564663,"text":"Now, imagine if I could look at all of you"},{"time":568154,"text":"and dial from real humans into elves."},{"time":572760,"text":"When technology truly\nunderstands our world,"},{"time":575548,"text":"it will again transform\nthe ways we interact,"},{"time":579219,"text":"the ways we work and the ways we play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587238,"text":"Less than half a century ago,"},{"time":589798,"text":"two courageous men landed on the moon,"},{"time":592696,"text":"using computers that were less powerful\nthan the phones in your pockets."},{"time":597110,"text":"Six hundred million humans watched them"},{"time":600245,"text":"on grainy, black-and-white televisions."},{"time":603579,"text":"And the world?"},{"time":605096,"text":"The world was mesmerized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608030,"text":"Now imagine how our children\nand their children"},{"time":612986,"text":"will experience the continued\nexploration of space"},{"time":616547,"text":"with technology\nthat understands this world."},{"time":621355,"text":"We already live in a world where\nreal-time universal translators exist."},{"time":626174,"text":"And I can squint, and I can already\nsee holographic telepresence"},{"time":631333,"text":"in our near future."},{"time":633079,"text":"In fact, since we've been lucky\nwith our demo so far,"},{"time":636182,"text":"let's try doing something else\neven more crazy."},{"time":639153,"text":"I invite you to experience,"},{"time":641930,"text":"for the first time anywhere in the world,"},{"time":644991,"text":"here on the TED stage,"},{"time":647500,"text":"a real-life holographic teleportation,"},{"time":651953,"text":"between me and my friend,\nDr. Jeffrey Norris,"},{"time":655684,"text":"from NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658506,"text":"Finger crossed. Hi, Jeff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662514,"text":"Jeff Norris: Hey, Alex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663704,"text":"Alex Kipman: Phew! That worked.\nHow are you doing today, Jeff?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666831,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668958,"text":"JN: Doing great. I had an awesome week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671046,"text":"AK: So, can you tell us a little bit,\nJeff, about where you are?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676197,"text":"JN: Well, I'm actually in three places."},{"time":679222,"text":"I'm standing in a room across the street,"},{"time":682127,"text":"while I'm standing on this stage with you,"},{"time":685155,"text":"while I'm standing on Mars,\na hundred million miles away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689981,"text":"AK: Wow, a hundred million\nmiles away. This is crazy!"},{"time":693697,"text":"Can you tell us a little bit more\nabout where all this data"},{"time":696507,"text":"from Mars is coming from?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700005,"text":"JN: Absolutely."},{"time":701481,"text":"This is a precise\nholographic replica of Mars,"},{"time":705591,"text":"built from data captured\nby the Curiosity Mars Rover,"},{"time":708795,"text":"that I can explore as easily\nas a place on Earth."},{"time":713056,"text":"Humans are natural explorers."},{"time":716334,"text":"We can instantly\nunderstand an environment,"},{"time":718919,"text":"just by being present in it."},{"time":721773,"text":"We've built tools like our Mars Rover"},{"time":723817,"text":"to extend our vision\nand lengthen our reach."},{"time":727441,"text":"But for decades,"},{"time":729576,"text":"we've explored from a seat\nbehind screens and keyboards."},{"time":734779,"text":"Now, we're leaping over all of that,"},{"time":737652,"text":"over the giant antennas\nand the relay satellites"},{"time":740879,"text":"and the vastness between worlds"},{"time":743178,"text":"to take our first steps on this landscape\nas if we were truly there."},{"time":749502,"text":"Today, a group of scientists\non our mission"},{"time":752114,"text":"are seeing Mars as never before --"},{"time":755522,"text":"an alien world made\na little more familiar,"},{"time":758863,"text":"because they're finally exploring it\nas humans should."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763225,"text":"But our dreams don't have to end\nwith making it just like being there."},{"time":767935,"text":"When we dial this real world\nto the virtual,"},{"time":770373,"text":"we can do magical things."},{"time":773092,"text":"We can see in invisible wavelengths"},{"time":775507,"text":"or teleport to the top of a mountain."},{"time":778882,"text":"Perhaps someday, we'll feel the minerals\nin a rock just by touching it."},{"time":785003,"text":"We're taking the first steps."},{"time":787177,"text":"But we want the whole world\nto join us in taking the next,"},{"time":790951,"text":"because this is not a journey for a few,"},{"time":793738,"text":"but for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796360,"text":"AK: Thank you Jeff, this was amazing."},{"time":798249,"text":"Thank you so much for joining us\non the TED stage today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801010,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807747,"text":"JN: Thank you Alex, bye bye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810483,"text":"AK: Bye, Jeff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818562,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825908,"text":"I dream about this future"},{"time":829145,"text":"every single day."},{"time":832080,"text":"I take inspiration from our ancestors."},{"time":834855,"text":"We used to live in tribes\nwhere we interacted,"},{"time":837404,"text":"communicated and worked together."},{"time":840509,"text":"We are all beginning to build technology\nthat will enable us to return"},{"time":845526,"text":"to the humanity that brought us\nwhere we are today --"},{"time":849419,"text":"technology that will let us stop living\ninside this 2D world"},{"time":854560,"text":"of monitors and pixels,"},{"time":856592,"text":"and let us start remembering\nwhat it feels like"},{"time":861363,"text":"to live in our 3D world."},{"time":865938,"text":"It's a phenomenal time to be human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870147,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871344,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":876437,"text":"Helen Walters: Thanks so much.\nI have some questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878958,"text":"AK: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880133,"text":"HW: So there's been\nsome talk in the press."},{"time":882579,"text":"And I'll just ask you straight,\nthen we have a straight answer."},{"time":885629,"text":"There's been talk about the difference\nbetween the demos"},{"time":888335,"text":"and the reality of the commercial product."},{"time":890541,"text":"Talk about this field of view issue."},{"time":892516,"text":"Is this type of experience what someone\nwho buys the product will get?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896859,"text":"AK: It's a great question,"},{"time":898842,"text":"Or, said better, this is a question\nwe've been receiving"},{"time":901517,"text":"in the media for possibly the last year."},{"time":904204,"text":"If you do your research,\nI haven't answered that question."},{"time":906975,"text":"I've purposely ignored it,"},{"time":908405,"text":"because ultimately,\nit's the wrong question to ask."},{"time":911535,"text":"That's the equivalent of me showing\nholograms to someone for the first time,"},{"time":917983,"text":"and you then saying,\n\"What's the size of your television?\""},{"time":921817,"text":"The field of view for the product\nis almost irrelevant."},{"time":924535,"text":"What we should be talking about\nis the density of lights,"},{"time":928057,"text":"or radiance, that shows up."},{"time":929867,"text":"Better said, what the angular resolution\nis of the things that you see."},{"time":933262,"text":"So from that perspective, what you saw --"},{"time":935286,"text":"you know, the camera\nis wearing a HoloLens."},{"time":937373,"text":"So even if I wanted to cheat, I can't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939381,"text":"HW: But the camera has a different lens\non it than our eye. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942971,"text":"AK: The camera has a fish-eye lens on it."},{"time":945915,"text":"It's seeing a much wider view\nthan the human eye is."},{"time":948860,"text":"So if you think about the points of light\nthat show up radially"},{"time":953189,"text":"from the vision of the camera,"},{"time":954727,"text":"which is the thing that matters:"},{"time":956472,"text":"how many points of light\ncan I get in a given volume?"},{"time":959054,"text":"That's the same as I get\non this HoloLens as I will on that one."},{"time":963205,"text":"Now, this camera sees\na much wider view of the world, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":968210,"text":"HW: Jesus Christ!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":969457,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":970482,"text":"AK: He did show up!\nI told you he'd show up."},{"time":972585,"text":"Come this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973808,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975696,"text":"HW: Oh, shit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977723,"text":"AK: And there's holographic Jeff Norris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980199,"text":"HW: I knew something was happening,\nbut I really wasn't sure what."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983841,"text":"AK: So in short: to be super crisp,"},{"time":985612,"text":"the camera that you see on the screen\nhas a wider field of view"},{"time":988652,"text":"than the human eye."},{"time":989874,"text":"But the angular resolution\nof the holograms that you see,"},{"time":993105,"text":"the points of light per unit of area,"},{"time":997098,"text":"are actually the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998288,"text":"HW: So you spent -- Jeff,\nI'll get to you in a minute --"},{"time":1001451,"text":"so you spent a lot of time\nmapping the stage --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006055,"text":"AK: That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007429,"text":"HW: So help me out here:"},{"time":1008627,"text":"if I buy a HoloLens and have it at home,"},{"time":1010620,"text":"I don't need to map my apartment, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012581,"text":"AK: The HoloLens maps in real time\nat about five frames per second,"},{"time":1016718,"text":"with this technology\nthat we call spatial mapping."},{"time":1019143,"text":"So in your home, as soon as you put it on,"},{"time":1021194,"text":"holograms will start showing up,\nand you'll start placing them"},{"time":1024148,"text":"and they'll start learning your home."},{"time":1025963,"text":"In a stage environment where we're trying\nto get something on my head"},{"time":1029496,"text":"to communicate with something over there"},{"time":1031671,"text":"with all of the wireless connectivity\nthat usually brings all conferences down,"},{"time":1035666,"text":"we don't take the risk\nof trying to do this live."},{"time":1040027,"text":"So what we do is pre-map the stage\nat five frames per second"},{"time":1043105,"text":"with the same spatial-mapping technology"},{"time":1045153,"text":"that you'll use with the product at home,"},{"time":1047164,"text":"and then we store it,"},{"time":1048339,"text":"so that when there's shenanigans\nof wireless in an environment like this,"},{"time":1051817,"text":"between the camera's HoloLens\nand the one on my head,"},{"time":1054858,"text":"we don't have things disappear."},{"time":1056475,"text":"Because ultimately, the holograms\nare coming from this HoloLens,"},{"time":1059928,"text":"and that one is just viewing the HoloLens."},{"time":1061992,"text":"So if I lose connectivity,"},{"time":1063941,"text":"you would stop seeing\nbeautiful things on the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066492,"text":"HW: And it was beautiful."},{"time":1068079,"text":"Um ... Jeff?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070538,"text":"JN: Yes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072367,"text":"HW: Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075543,"text":"AK: I'll take a step back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076818,"text":"HW: So Jeff, you were on Mars,"},{"time":1079772,"text":"you were here, you were\nin a room across the street."},{"time":1082303,"text":"Tell me more about the fact that,\nwith holograms, you have sight"},{"time":1086529,"text":"but you don't have touch,\nyou don't have smell."},{"time":1089254,"text":"Is this scientifically useful now?"},{"time":1092824,"text":"That's my question for a hologram."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095044,"text":"JN: Thanks for the question."},{"time":1096864,"text":"Absolutely, I believe\nthat these technologies"},{"time":1099401,"text":"are scientifically useful right now,"},{"time":1101449,"text":"and that's why we're using them\nin multiple parts of our work at NASA."},{"time":1106077,"text":"So we're using it to improve\nthe ways that we explore Mars."},{"time":1109720,"text":"We're also using it for our astronauts\non the space station."},{"time":1113205,"text":"We're even using it now to design"},{"time":1115681,"text":"the next generation of our spacecraft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118834,"text":"HW: Amazing. OK, Jeff, please go away.\nThank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121892,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124125,"text":"Alex, really, that was amazing.\nThank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1127636,"text":"AK: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1128818,"text":"HW: Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130103,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}